cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER. 

The paper deals with analyzing credibility, trust, and expertise in news communities, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and social network analysis. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also deals with the fairness and style of reporting, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and the bias of community members, which falls under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
